<h5 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h5>
<p>Use the substitution <span class="process-math">\(z=Rv-Mg\text{,}\)</span> to rewrite the above equation as</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\frac{\frac{1}{R}\dx{z}}{z}=-\frac{1}{m}\dx{t}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">and show that</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
v=\frac{Mg}{R}+\left(v_0-\frac{Mg}{R}\right)e^{-\frac{r}{m}t}.
\end{equation*}
</div>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-4.html#p-53" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
